Not sure it is a bug or an intended behavior.

When I want to create a fixed size borderless window, but it seems to ignore the window position I set.

The engine parameters are below
```
    engineParameters_[EP_BORDERLESS] = true;
    engineParameters_[EP_WINDOW_POSITION_X] = 100;
    engineParameters_[EP_WINDOW_POSITION_Y] = 100;
    engineParameters_[EP_WINDOW_WIDTH] = 500;
    engineParameters_[EP_WINDOW_HEIGHT] = 500;
```
I get the below result:
![4_h 9z kzvt0n_ gxtjj](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/25144819/26776667/b1b00c70-4a0c-11e7-966f-4d99208d21a4.png)

CONTACT and PhysicsEndContact2D::P_CONTACT event parameters. Fixed #1958. Fixed #1965.

BTW, there is one more step possible that I am unsure about.
I can remove P_CONTACT parameter from other events too.

**Cons:**
- Broken compatibility.

**Pros:**
+ Encapsulation of b2 internals;
+ Consistency of event parameters;
+ Avoid misuse of b2Contact;
+ This stuff is unusable from scripts anyway;

Or (at least) consider this parameter as deprecated and remove it in the future.

I also want to rename recently added P_CONTACTPOINTS to P_CONTACTS (like in bullet physics events).
I've chosen first name to avoid ambigity with P_CONTACT. However, if P_CONTACT is deprecated and almost useless, ambigity doesn't matter very much.

If one uses Node->LookAt() of quat.FromLookRotation() they find-out that both node and quat
look in reverse direction from what it was intended to. While operated in global coordinates,
this one might be really confusing. Found this while trying to rotate head and chest bone in direction of player. Tried with Quaternion first, but had to reverse direction. Was confused a bit and then tried with
Node->LookAt and found the same issue. A long time ago I tried these and they were working
(in the same circumstances) so I wonder what is going on. I could not find any proof I'm doing something
wrong here, so I submit a bug. The code is simple:

```c++
void BTBlackboard::HandleSceneDrawableUpdateFinished(Urho3D::StringHash eventType, Urho3D::VariantMap& eventData)
{
        Node *head = node_->GetChild("head", true);
        Node *spine = node_->GetChild("spine02", true);
        Node *root = node_->GetChild("root", true);
        if (look_at_enabled && look_at) {
                Node *lookat_target = look_at;
                if (look_at->HasTag("player")) {
                        VariantMap vars = look_at->GetVars();
                        bool first_person = vars["first_persin"].GetBool();
                        if (first_person)
                                lookat_target = (Node *) vars["camera_node"].GetPtr();
                        else {
                                lookat_target = look_at->GetChild("head", true);
                        }
                } else {
                        lookat_target = look_at->GetChild("head", true);
                }
                if (!lookat_target)
                        lookat_target = look_at;
                URHO3D_LOGINFO("looking at: " + lookat_target->GetName() + " " + lookat_target->GetWorldPosition().ToString());
                URHO3D_LOGINFO("from: " +  head->GetWorldPosition().ToString());
                Quaternion prep;
                Vector3 dir = -(lookat_target->GetWorldPosition() - node_->GetWorldPosition() - Vector3(0.0f, 0.7f, 0.0f));
                URHO3D_LOGINFO("dir: " +  dir.ToString());
                prep.FromLookRotation(dir, Vector3(0.0f, 1.0f, 0.0f));
                Quaternion rot = root->GetWorldRotation();
//              Quaternion head_initial = head->GetParent()->GetWorldRotation().Inv();
//              Quaternion rot = spine->GetWorldRotation();
////            spine->SetWorldRotation(rot.Slerp(prep * Quaternion(0.0f, -180.0f, 0.0f), 0.5));
                spine->SetWorldRotation(rot.Slerp(prep, 0.5));
//              Quaternion rotl = head->GetWorldRotation();
////            head->SetWorldRotation(prep * Quaternion(0.0f, -180.0f, 0.0f));
///             Quaternion correction(-15.0f, 0.0f, 0.0f);
////            head->SetWorldRotation(prep);
                head->LookAt(lookat_target->GetWorldPosition());
        }
}
```
